  "content": "<p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">YAML is used to store the data and not command.(like if-else) it is Similiar to XML &amp; JSON\n\n\n\nData Serialization</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p>Serialization-is&nbsp; the process of making a data&nbsp; as a stream and&nbsp; &nbsp;for applying&nbsp; it to variious devices&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>object is a combination of code and data</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>Data Serialization Languages arw:Yaml,Json,Xml</p><p><br></p><p>Used in Kubernetes configuration files,Docker too,Caches,Logs etc.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>-&gt; key value pairs</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>Yaml is case sensitive and its indendation is very important</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>seprate the document from&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">---</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">to end the file use -triple dot -(...)<br><br><br>we have only one line&nbsp; another of the same sentence considered as error</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">if you want to write like in 2 lines then use | symbol to use it</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">to write the things as double line&nbsp; then we should use &gt; to write it in multiple lines&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">XML-Extensible MarkUp Language</span></p><p>&nbsp;1. data can be feed to any type of application</p><p><br></p><p>JSON :&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>[] - represents collection.</p><p>{}= represents individual entity</p><p><br></p><p>json to&nbsp; YAML website is avaiable :</p><p>eg school.json ----&gt; school.yaml</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>While sending the data into the&nbsp; Kubernetes the YAML files needs to be&nbsp; validated hence<span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\">tools datree- validates config files of kubernetes and YAML files,monacle - helps manage YAML like navigators,Lens - have pre written code&nbsp; &nbsp;it has all prebuilt code&nbsp; within it&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: var(--vscode-editor-background); color: var(--vscode-editor-foreground); font-weight: var(--vscode-font-weight);\"><br></span></p><p><br></p>",
